The paper deals with the problem of characterizing the equivalence of binary asymmetric channels from the point of view of maximum likelihood decoding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and probability (cs.ITP). The paper also involves partitioning the space of parameters into regions, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions applications to decoding problems, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
